               <p>GEORGE WELLS. I live in Newman-street, Oxford-street. On Sunday, the 5th of April, about five o'clock in the evening, I was coming out of <placeName id="t18180506-44-crimeloc249">Hyde Park, at the small gate, in Oxford-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18180506-44-crimeloc249" type="placeName" value="Hyde Park, at the small gate, in Oxford-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18180506-44-crimeloc249" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180506-44-off247 t18180506-44-crimeloc249"></join>, the prisoner was close behind me - I felt something at my coat-pocket, and missed my handkerchief; the prisoner pushed by me, and turned into the park again at the carriage gate. I pursued, caught him, and found my handkerchief concealed in the back of his trowsers - He begged for mercy.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. PLATT. I have seen his friends, who are respectable people; I believe he is a good character.</p>
               <p>
